description: Using a multimeter, test for electrical continuity across the switch and relevant internal PCB traces/components inside Control Module 6 while the module is still in-circuit and the switch is ON. This will determine if there is an internal open circuit or fault within the module blocking voltage propagation., outcome="All tested switches and cables show nominal continuity with resistances at or near their expected values, indicating no internal open circuits within the module or its components. However, 'Control Input Cable (+) 6' has one end (port 'n') disconnected and floating, which is a wiring anomaly. No polarity inversion was identified in the tested connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=110.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
